1
00:00:22,289 --> 00:00:25,857
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>                
<i>SORRY ABOUT THE PRINCIPAL NOT</i>   
<i>BEING ABLE TO GIVE YOU THE TOUR.</i>


2
00:00:25,926 --> 00:00:27,859
        HE'S REAL BUSY.         


3
00:00:27,928 --> 00:00:31,296
    WORKING UP                  
    THE SCHOOL LUNCH SCHEDULE   
    IS TRYING WORK, I'M SURE.   


4
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:35,200
THIS WAS MR. JAROD'S CLASSROOM. 
HE WAS, LIKE,                   
THE BEST SUBSTITUTE.            


5
00:00:35,269 --> 00:00:38,170
KIDS WOULD SIT IN               
ON THE CLASS EVEN THOUGH        
THEY WEREN'T ENROLLED.          


6
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:40,172
AND HE DID                      
THE COOLEST EXPERIMENTS.        


7
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:42,708
                I CAN SEE THAT. 
OH, YEAH.                       


8
00:00:42,777 --> 00:00:47,179
<i>WE EVEN DID</i>                     
<i>A VIROLOGY UNIT ON BUGS</i>         
<i>TO LEARN THEIR RESILIENCY.</i>      


9
00:00:47,248 --> 00:00:51,083
HE TOLD US THAT ROACHES         
WOULD BE THE ONLY LIVING THING  
AFTER A BIOLOGICAL HOLOCAUST--  


10
00:00:51,152 --> 00:00:54,219
            THEM AND SOME WOMAN 
            NAMED PARKER.       


11
00:00:55,689 --> 00:00:57,856
HARDLY SOUNDS LIKE              
HIGH SCHOOL BIOLOGY.            


12
00:00:57,925 --> 00:01:00,259
    MR. JAROD, LIKE,            
    MARCHED TO HIS OWN DRUMMER. 


13
00:01:00,327 --> 00:01:02,694
HE'S A ONE-MAN BAND, ALL RIGHT. 


14
00:01:02,762 --> 00:01:05,096
        THE BEST PART IS        
        HE WOULDN'T GRADE US.   


15
00:01:05,165 --> 00:01:08,633
IT WAS LIKE HE WAS              
CONDUCTING HIS OWN EXPERIMENT,  


16
00:01:08,702 --> 00:01:10,969
        <i> AND WE WERE COLLECTING</i> 
        <i> THE DATA FOR HIM.</i>      


17
00:01:11,038 --> 00:01:13,471
YOU RUN ALONG                   
TO HOMEROOM NOW.                


18
00:01:34,061 --> 00:01:35,426
                AAH!            


19
00:01:37,430 --> 00:01:39,397
    <i> CARLOS?</i>                    


20
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:42,234
    WAIT! COME BACK HERE!       


21
00:01:42,303 --> 00:01:45,437
        HOLD IT RIGHT THERE!    
        COME ON, NOW! STOP!     


22
00:01:45,505 --> 00:01:49,507
            CARLOS, COME ON!    
            THAT'S IT!          
            AAH!                


23
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:51,910
WHERE'S YOUR DAD?               
    DOWN THE HALL, LAST ROOM.   


24
00:02:08,395 --> 00:02:10,862
    MY NAME IS JAROD.           


25
00:02:10,931 --> 00:02:13,932
YOU'RE GOING TO BE JUST FINE.   


26
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,503
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


27
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:05,317
    OKAY, THE FATHER'S SYMPTOMS 
    INCLUDE WEIGHT LOSS, FEVER, 


28
00:03:05,386 --> 00:03:07,586
    NIGHT SWEATS, VIOLENT COUGH,
    SWOLLEN LYMPH NODES--       


29
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:10,889
<i>MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS.</i>     
                LOOKS LIKE IT.  


30
00:03:10,958 --> 00:03:13,358
YOU DON'T SEE THAT              
MUCH ANYMORE.                   
                            NO. 


31
00:03:13,426 --> 00:03:17,095
    BUT HE'LL BE FINE           
    ONCE WE GET HIM ADMITTED.   
HOW'S THE BOY?                  


32
00:03:17,164 --> 00:03:20,932
        TOO EARLY TO TELL.      
        BUT MUCH BETTER OFF     
        THAN YOU'RE GONNA BE... 


33
00:03:21,001 --> 00:03:23,534
    ONCE GARBER FINDS OUT       
    WHAT YOU DID WITH THE KID.  


34
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:32,677
VIOLATING QUARANTINE PROCEDURES 
WITH THESE PEOPLE               
WAS DAMN FOOLISH.               


35
00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:34,679
I REALIZE IT WAS                
A BIT UNORTHODOX, SIR,          


36
00:03:34,748 --> 00:03:37,281
    BUT T.B. IS                 
    A LEVEL 2 CLASSIFICATION.   


37
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:39,550
    IT DOESN'T REQUIRE          
    AN ON-SITE QUARANTINE.      


38
00:03:39,619 --> 00:03:43,021
FRIENDLY ADVICE, DR. REILLY.    
IF YOU DON'T WANNA END UP DEAD, 
YOU'LL REMEMBER THAT...         


39
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:45,990
EVERY ONE OF THESE SITUATIONS   
SHOULD BE TREATED               
AS A LEVEL 4 SITUATION.         


40
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:51,663
<i>WALTER, WHETHER OR NOT THE BOY</i>  
<i>WAS ALREADY EXPOSED, OR--</i>       
<i>WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?</i>   


41
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:55,200
<i>- HE'S PROTECTED EITHER WAY.</i>    
<i>- [ Jarod ] AND THE BOY GETS</i>    
<i>  TO BE WITH HIS FATHER NOW.</i>    


42
00:03:55,269 --> 00:03:57,235
I FELT LIKE HE NEEDED THAT.     


43
00:03:57,304 --> 00:04:00,972
    GREAT. OUR NEW GUY'S        
    FLORENCE NIGHTINGALE.       


44
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:06,811
<i>[ Man Coughing ]</i>                
<i>YEAH, YOU'RE GONNA</i>              
<i>LOVE THIS PLACE.</i>                


45
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:10,147
STOVE AND OVEN IN THE KITCHEN,  
HOT AND COLD RUNNING.           


46
00:04:10,216 --> 00:04:14,218
    170 A MONTH PLUS UTILITIES. 


47
00:04:14,287 --> 00:04:18,189
170?                            
                    OKAY, 150.  


48
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,191
    I'LL PAY THE WATER.         
    COME ON DOWN TO THE OFFICE. 


49
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:22,761
        WE'LL SIGN THE PAPERS.  
DOES IT HAVE ROACHES?           


50
00:04:22,829 --> 00:04:27,665
    OF COURSE NOT. THIS PLACE   
    IS A BOHEMIAN'S DREAM,      
    NOT SOME SLUM.              


51
00:04:27,735 --> 00:04:29,568
        COME ON TO THE OFFICE.  
NO ROACHES?                     


52
00:04:29,636 --> 00:04:32,837
<i>♪♪ [ Violin ]</i>                   


53
00:04:32,906 --> 00:04:36,574
                        DAMN IT!
WHAT IS THAT?                   


54
00:04:36,643 --> 00:04:40,979
            IT'S A NEVER-ENDIN' 
            CAT-GUT NIGHTMARE   
            IS WHAT IT IS,      


55
00:04:41,048 --> 00:04:44,849
    NOT TO MENTION              
    THE WORST RENTAL DECISION...


56
00:04:44,918 --> 00:04:46,918
                    <i> OF MY LIFE!</i>


57
00:04:46,986 --> 00:04:50,388
                <i> [ Baby Crying ]</i>


58
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:53,758
        THERE'S ANOTHER BUILDING
        TWO BLOCKS WEST OF HERE.


59
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:56,260
        MIGHT BE ABLE TO FIND   
        SOMETHIN' QUIETER THERE.


60
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:59,764
NO. I'LL TAKE THIS PLACE.       


61
00:04:59,832 --> 00:05:03,134
IT'S A LOT NICER                
THAN WHERE I USED TO LIVE.      


62
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:10,141
        [ Sneezes ]             


63
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:12,143
            BLESS YOU.          
            SOUNDS LIKE THE FLU.


64
00:05:12,212 --> 00:05:14,779
IT'S COLD AND RAINY IN PORTLAND 
THIS TIME OF YEAR.              


65
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:19,584
                HERE, KEEP IT.  
                IT'S CLEAN.     


66
00:05:19,652 --> 00:05:23,755
SO I TOOK A TRIP WITHOUT YOU.   
DON'T TELL ME YOU'RE JEALOUS.   


67
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:26,791
                    CONFUSED.   


68
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:29,360
            I THOUGHT WE WERE   
            WORKING TOGETHER.   


69
00:05:29,429 --> 00:05:32,697
SO DID I,                       
UNTIL I DISCOVERED              
YOUR PERSONAL ADS...            


70
00:05:32,766 --> 00:05:36,167
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY            
TRYING TO CONTACT JAROD.        


71
00:05:36,236 --> 00:05:38,169
I DON'T LIKE SECRETS.           


72
00:05:38,238 --> 00:05:40,972
    WELL, HE WASN'T ANSWERING   
    MY E-MAIL MESSAGES,         
    SO I TRIED ANOTHER TACK.    


73
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:44,242
BUT I WOULD HAVE LET YOU KNOW   
IF HE HAD CONTACTED ME.         


74
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:46,244
    I HAVE A FEVER, SYD--       
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>                  


75
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:48,880
        <i> BUT IT'S NOT BAD ENOUGH</i>
        <i> TO BELIEVE THAT.</i>       


76
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,283
            WHAT?               
UM--                            


77
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:55,954
[ Clears Throat ]               
HE'S IN THE LAB.                


78
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,356
            WHO?                


79
00:05:58,424 --> 00:06:00,458
MR. RAINES.                     


80
00:06:02,896 --> 00:06:05,097
MR. RAINES HASN'T BEEN          
IN THE LAB IN 10 YEARS.         


81
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:07,598
WELL, UH, HE'S IN THERE NOW,    


82
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,668
<i>AND HE'S LOOKING FOR YOU TWO.</i>   


83
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:12,771
SO, GOOD LUCK.                  


84
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:15,473
<i>[ Labored Breathing ]</i>           


85
00:06:19,213 --> 00:06:22,981
                    MR. RAINES? 
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING.      


86
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:25,951
WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT            
SOMETHING SO BEAUTIFUL          
COULD BE REPLICATED...          


87
00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:31,022
BY A FOUR-YEAR-OLD BOY          
IN ONLY TWO HOURS?              


88
00:06:31,091 --> 00:06:34,292
    <i> JAROD WAS BRILLIANT</i>        
    <i> THE DAY HE GOT HERE.</i>       


89
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:36,828
    <i> HE WAS BRILLIANT</i>           
    <i> THE DAY HE ESCAPED.</i>        


90
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:39,730
        <i> AND THE QUESTION IS,</i>   


91
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:42,533
            WHERE IS HE?        


92
00:06:42,602 --> 00:06:45,670
        MR. RAINES, JAROD       
        HAS BEEN HARDER TO CATCH
        THAN WE THOUGHT.        


93
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,706
SYDNEY, WE NEED HIM.            


94
00:06:48,775 --> 00:06:52,410
        I KNOW.                 
                    [ Sneezes ] 


95
00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:55,046
    [ Coughs ]                  


96
00:06:55,115 --> 00:06:57,048
        MAY I?                  


97
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:02,053
                MR. RAINES,     
                I HAVE THE FLU. 


98
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,958
    I'M DYING.                  


99
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:10,228
        MMM.                    


100
00:07:11,298 --> 00:07:13,331
<i>[ Coughing ]</i>                    


101
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:17,235
                        KEEP IT.


102
00:07:17,304 --> 00:07:20,839
    BRING JAROD BACK            
    WHERE HE BELONGS,           


103
00:07:21,975 --> 00:07:24,842
<i>OR I'LL GET SOMEONE WHO WILL.</i>   


104
00:07:24,911 --> 00:07:26,877
    ARE WE CLEAR?               


105
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:29,047
            MY FATHER           
            WANTS ME TO DO IT.  


106
00:07:29,116 --> 00:07:32,617
UNLIKE EVERYONE ELSE            
AROUND HERE,                    


107
00:07:32,685 --> 00:07:35,653
I'M NOT AFRAID OF YOUR FATHER.  


108
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,057
            <i> I DON'T HAVE TO BE.</i>


109
00:07:42,929 --> 00:07:45,796
<i>[ Garber ]</i>                      
<i>OUR JOB HERE AT RIDA</i>            
<i>IS TO CONTAIN VIRAL OUTBREAKS...</i>


110
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:47,798
            <i> BEFORE THEY SPREAD.</i>


111
00:07:47,868 --> 00:07:50,501
            I'VE SEEN THE WORST 
            THAT A VIRUS CAN DO,
            AND BECAUSE OF IT,  


112
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:52,837
                BY THE NUMBERS  
                IS USUALLY BEST.


113
00:07:52,906 --> 00:07:55,773
IN RETROSPECT,                  
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING         
WITH BRIGGS AND HIS SON, JAROD. 


114
00:07:55,842 --> 00:07:59,311
    LISTEN, I WAS OUT OF LINE.  


115
00:07:59,379 --> 00:08:01,847
IT'S ALL RIGHT.                 


116
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:04,015
        WELL, YOUR CREDENTIALS  
        ARE IMPRESSIVE.         


117
00:08:04,084 --> 00:08:06,351
            A STINT IN BAMRID   
            IN LONDON,          


118
00:08:06,419 --> 00:08:08,887
        M.D./Ph.D IN VIROLOGY.  


119
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:11,189
WHERE DID YOU DO YOUR DOCTORATE,
BY THE WAY?                     


120
00:08:11,258 --> 00:08:13,725
HORACE GREELEY HIGH SCHOOL,     
PORTLAND.                       
                [ Chuckling ]   


121
00:08:17,197 --> 00:08:19,530
THE DOOR'S UNDER                
NEGATIVE AIR PRESSURE           
TO CONTAIN LEAKS.               


122
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:21,833
            YEAH, WE PIONEERED  
            THE TECHNIQUE HERE. 


123
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:26,271
I NOTICED IN YOUR FILE          
THAT YOU WERE VACCINATED FOR    
ANTHRAX AND THE W.E.E. SERIES.  


124
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,773
I WAS WORKING IN THE GULF       
WITH NATO's Q.R.T.,             


125
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,942
AND THE W.E.E. WAS FOR          
THE PEKOWSKY SYNDROME           
IN JOHANNESBURG.                


126
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:34,513
        A FRIGHTENING SCENARIO. 
YES, VERY.                      


127
00:08:34,581 --> 00:08:37,716
WATCHING SOMEBODY SUFFER        
CAN HAVE AN EFFECT ON YOU.      


128
00:08:37,784 --> 00:08:40,018
I HOPE I CAN MAKE               
A DIFFERENCE HERE.              


129
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:43,922
                    [ Beeping ] 


130
00:08:43,991 --> 00:08:47,158
[ Female Electronic Voice ]     
CODE ACCEPTED.                  


131
00:08:47,227 --> 00:08:50,161
        JAROD, JEFF BAYTOS,     


132
00:08:50,230 --> 00:08:52,864
DECONTAMINATION                 
AND FACILITIES SPECIALIST.      


133
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:56,834
    - NICE TO MEET YOU.         
    - UH, IX-NAY ON             
      THE ANDSHAKE-HAY, DOC.    


134
00:08:56,903 --> 00:09:01,205
[ Chuckling ]                   
MR. BAYTOS TENDS                
TO BE OVERCAUTIOUS.             


135
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:03,207
        NO SUCH THING           
        IN A PLACE LIKE THIS.   


136
00:09:03,276 --> 00:09:05,209
        ONE WRONG MOVE          
        LIKE PRESSING THE FLESH,


137
00:09:05,278 --> 00:09:08,846
    AND, UH,                    
    IT'S OFF TO THE SUBMARINE   
    FOR 10,000 YEARS.           


138
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:10,815
YOU CALL YOUR MORGUE            
THE "SUBMARINE"?                


139
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,784
    WHAT DID YOU CALL IT        
    AT BAMRID?                  


140
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:15,319
        CHERNOBYL.              


141
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:19,123
    WELL, WE'RE WORKING         
    A LEVEL 3 TODAY.            


142
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:23,227
AN OFFSHOOT STRAIN              
OF RIFT VALLEY FEVER.           


143
00:09:23,296 --> 00:09:25,230
YOU READY TO BATTLE             
THE UNSEEN ENEMY?               


144
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:27,231
        ABSOLUTELY.             


145
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:29,500
WILL YOU BE JOINING US,         
MR. BAYTOS?                     


146
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:33,004
            LEVEL 2 IS          
            MY LIMIT NOW, MAN.  


147
00:09:37,844 --> 00:09:40,412
LIVE LONG AND PROSPER.          


148
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,480
            <i> [ Garber Chuckles ]</i>


149
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:46,451
        BAYTOS WITNESSED A MAN  
        DIE OF EBOLA.           


150
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:49,487
    HE'S BEEN RELUCTANT TO GO   
    PAST LEVEL 2 EVER SINCE.    


151
00:09:49,556 --> 00:09:51,989
    <i> FORTUNATELY,</i>               
    <i> HE'S THE BEST THERE IS...</i>  


152
00:09:52,058 --> 00:09:54,159
    WHEN IT COMES TO DECON.     


153
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:43,574
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>IT'S NICE TO HAVE VISITORS.</i>     


154
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:47,979
<i>OUR FRIENDS DON'T KNOW</i>          
<i>WHAT TO THINK OR SAY,</i>           
<i>SO THEY JUST STAY AWAY.</i>         


155
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:50,114
        <i> DID YOU MEET JON</i>       
        <i> IN SOUTH AFRICA?</i>       


156
00:10:50,183 --> 00:10:52,550
                NO, BUT I HEARD 
                A LOT ABOUT HIM.


157
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:56,087
        WE WERE BOTH WORKING    
        ON SEPARATE STRIKE TEAMS
        IN THE MUTABA VILLAGE.  


158
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:59,757
        OH. YOU KNOW,           
        HE LOVED THAT JOB.      


159
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:03,261
    HE WAS THE FIRST TO ARRIVE  
    AND THE LAST TO LEAVE.      


160
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:08,599
HE'D STAY IN PLACES             
WHERE THERE WAS NO HOPE,        
NO CHANCE TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE. 


161
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,469
HOLDING THE HAND OF A DYING MAN 
TO LET HIM KNOW HE'S NOT ALONE--


162
00:11:11,538 --> 00:11:14,072
                <i> THAT'S MAKING</i>  
                <i> A DIFFERENCE.</i>  


163
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:17,942
I'M WORKING WITH WALTER GARBER  
NOW. I'M TRYING TO FINISH       
THE WORK YOUR HUSBAND STARTED.  


164
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,945
    WELL, YOU'RE LUCKY          
    TO BE WORKING UNDER WALTER. 


165
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:24,581
<i>JON THOUGHT THE WORLD OF HIM.</i>   
<i>THAT'S THEM AT</i>                  
<i>THE W.H.O. BANQUET.</i>             


166
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:26,584
                <i> [ Door Opens ]</i> 


167
00:11:26,653 --> 00:11:29,020
<i>HEY, YOU'RE SUPPOSED</i>            
<i>TO BE NAPPING.</i>                  


168
00:11:29,089 --> 00:11:31,755
        I THOUGHT I HEARD DADDY.


169
00:11:31,824 --> 00:11:33,791
NO, IT'S NOT DADDY.             
IT'S JUST A FRIEND.             


170
00:11:35,595 --> 00:11:38,663
    - OH.                       
    - HI. MY NAME'S JAROD.      


171
00:11:38,732 --> 00:11:41,098
    - HI.                       
    - GO LIE DOWN, HONEY.       


172
00:11:42,835 --> 00:11:45,836
    <i> THIS HAS BEEN</i>              
    <i> ESPECIALLY HARD ON HER.</i>    


173
00:11:48,408 --> 00:11:51,809
HE VANISHED RIGHT BEFORE        
HER BIRTHDAY.                   


174
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:55,846
HOW DO I EXPLAIN THAT TO CINDY? 


175
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:58,816
    I MEAN,                     
    HOW DO I EXPLAIN ANY OF IT? 


176
00:11:58,885 --> 00:12:01,419
        YOU KNOW, I-I KNOW      
        HE'S NOT COMING BACK.   


177
00:12:01,488 --> 00:12:04,288
        YOU KNOW,               
        I-I'VE ACCEPTED THAT.   
        I HAVE.                 


178
00:12:06,359 --> 00:12:11,161
        I JUST, UH, WISH I KNEW 
        WHERE TO GO FROM HERE.  


179
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,164
            I MEAN,             
            HOW TO GO FROM HERE.


180
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:16,867
        <i> I MEAN, IS HE DEAD?</i>    
        <i> IS HE ALIVE?</i>           


181
00:12:20,139 --> 00:12:22,239
THAT'S A VERY BEAUTIFUL RING.   


182
00:12:23,542 --> 00:12:25,943
        JON DESIGNED            
        OUR WEDDING BANDS.      


183
00:12:26,012 --> 00:12:31,515
YOU KNOW, I KNOW IT'S CORNY,    
BUT HE WANTED THEM TO BE        
THE ONLY TWO ALIKE IN THE WORLD.


184
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:42,460
HERE. JON WORE THIS WHEN        
HE WENT INTO THE FIELD TO WORK. 


185
00:12:42,529 --> 00:12:45,930
HE NEVER GOT SICK WEARING IT.   
I'D LIKE YOU TO HAVE IT.        
                    I--         


186
00:12:45,999 --> 00:12:48,933
            I COULDN'T POSSIBLY 
            ACCEPT THAT.        


187
00:12:49,002 --> 00:12:52,703
NO, HE'D HAVE WANTED            
SOMEBODY WHO CARED              
AS MUCH AS HE DID TO HAVE IT.   


188
00:12:54,474 --> 00:12:58,242
                    THANK YOU.  
        YOU'RE WELCOME.         


189
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:22,634
    FITS LIKE A GLOVE.          


190
00:13:32,612 --> 00:13:35,580
<i>[ Chatter, Indistinct ]</i>         


191
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:44,956
    EXCUSE ME. I WAS WONDERING  
    IF YOU MIGHT HELP ME.       
UH, SURE. WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?   


192
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:49,593
IT SAYS HERE THAT               
THIS IS A-A MOTEL FOR ROACHES?  


193
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:53,631
    YEAH. IT'S LIKE, UH,        
    THE HOTEL CALIFORNIA...     


194
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,833
FOR OUR LITTLE                  
SIX-LEGGED FRIENDS, YOU KNOW?   


195
00:13:55,902 --> 00:13:57,435
HOTEL CALIFORNIA?               


196
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:01,572
YEAH, THEY CAN CHECK OUT        
ANYTIME THEY LIKE,              
BUT THEY CAN NEVER LEAVE.       


197
00:14:01,641 --> 00:14:03,941
        OH.                     


198
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:06,844
    OH! LIKE A TRAP.            


199
00:14:08,214 --> 00:14:11,149
    YEAH.                       
    SOMETHIN' LIKE THAT.        
        <i> WELL, THAT'S PERFECT.</i>  


200
00:14:11,218 --> 00:14:13,250
    I'LL TAKE 100.              


201
00:14:13,319 --> 00:14:15,586
        RIGHT ON.               


202
00:14:15,655 --> 00:14:19,590
<i>♪♪ [ Trumpet ]</i>                  
<i>[ Pounding On Wall ]</i>            


203
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:21,825
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>I'M GONNA WRAP THAT THING</i>       
<i>AROUND YOUR NECK...</i>             


204
00:14:21,894 --> 00:14:24,262
<i>IF YOU DON'T SHUT UP!</i>           


205
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:27,532
        COME AND GET IT.        


206
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,534
<i>[ Pounding ]</i>                    
<i>YOU'RE A DEAD MAN, HANSEL!</i>      


207
00:14:32,105 --> 00:14:34,238
        COME AND GET IT.        


208
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:36,340
<i>♪♪ [ Trumpet ]</i>                  


209
00:14:42,182 --> 00:14:45,015
            <i> [ Man ]</i>            
            <i> I'VE PAID MY RENT.</i> 
            <i> YOU CAN'T EVICT ME.</i>


210
00:14:45,085 --> 00:14:47,885
SIR, MY NAME IS JAROD.          
I'M YOUR NEIGHBOR.              


211
00:14:47,954 --> 00:14:52,356
I-I JUST WANTED TO TELL YOU     
THAT I'M VERY INTRIGUED         
BY YOUR MUSIC.                  


212
00:14:52,425 --> 00:14:55,726
    <i> I'M NOT FALLING FOR THAT!</i>  


213
00:14:55,795 --> 00:15:00,231
I WOULD VERY MUCH LIKE          
TO MEET YOU, AND I WOULD        
LIKE TO ASK YOU A QUESTION.     


214
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,500
            <i> [ Chain Rattling ]</i> 


215
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,008
            ARE YOU HERE        
            TO GIVE ME THE BOOT?


216
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:15,679
I WASN'T PLANNING ON IT, SIR,   
BUT YOU'RE MORE                 
THAN WELCOME TO MINE.           


217
00:15:18,484 --> 00:15:20,417
                    COME IN.    


218
00:15:25,057 --> 00:15:27,157
    IT'S NICE TO HAVE           
    A FRIENDLY AUDIENCE         
    FOR A CHANGE.               


219
00:15:27,226 --> 00:15:29,594
        BEN HANSEL'S THE NAME.  


220
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:34,232
BEN, I NEED YOUR HELP.          
                AND I YOURS.    
                DO YOU PLAY?    


221
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,967
I'VE CONDUCTED A SYMPHONY       
HERE AND THERE.                 


222
00:15:37,036 --> 00:15:42,139
        AH!                     
        WELL, THEN WHAT DO YOU  
        THINK OF THIS?          


223
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:46,944
♪♪ [ Loud, Harsh ]              


224
00:15:50,984 --> 00:15:55,219
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>SHUT UP!</i>                        
<i>YOU'RE DRIVING ME CRAZY!</i>        


225
00:15:55,288 --> 00:15:57,888
            CULTURAL DWARVES,   
            ALL OF THEM.        
<i>[ Man ] YOU SUCK!</i>               


226
00:15:57,957 --> 00:15:59,957
THAT'S VERY INTERESTING.        


227
00:16:00,025 --> 00:16:02,893
HAYDN'S                         
"CELLO CONCERTO IN 'C' MAJOR,"  
I BELIEVE.                      


228
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:07,297
I REWROTE IT FOR TRUMPET.       
I'M WORKING ON AN ARRANGEMENT   
FOR GLOCKENSPIEL.               


229
00:16:07,366 --> 00:16:09,600
        AN ARTIST MUST STRETCH, 
        YOU KNOW.               
YES.                            


230
00:16:09,669 --> 00:16:12,603
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN          
A MUSICIAN?                     
            FIFTEEN-ODD YEARS.  


231
00:16:12,672 --> 00:16:15,239
    THAT'S A LONG TIME.         


232
00:16:15,308 --> 00:16:20,577
    BUT IT'LL ALL BE WORTH IT   
    WHEN THE PHILHARMONIC CALLS.


233
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:23,648
            <i> I SENT THEM A TAPE</i> 
            <i> ABOUT A WEEK AGO.</i>  


234
00:16:23,716 --> 00:16:27,484
    YOU-- YOU HAD A QUESTION.   
    YES.                        


235
00:16:27,553 --> 00:16:31,655
I'M TRYING TO ATTRACT ROACHES,  
AND THIS DOESN'T SEEM TO WORK.  
DO YOU HAVE ANY?                


236
00:16:31,724 --> 00:16:36,160
        ROACHES?                
        I CAN'T GET RID OF THEM.


237
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:41,331
        I SPILLED A BOX OF      
        CRUNCHY CRAWLERS CEREAL 
        BEHIND THE FRIDGE ONCE. 


238
00:16:41,401 --> 00:16:43,768
        NOW EVERY NIGHT,        
        THEY COME OUT HUNTING.  


239
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:47,705
CRUNCHY CRAWLERS?               
        "THEY'RE                
         GROTESQUELY DELICIOUS."


240
00:16:47,773 --> 00:16:50,273
    YOU KNOW, I WAS WONDERING   
    ABOUT MY INTERPRETATION     
    OF THE FIRST MOVEMENT.      


241
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:52,276
            IT WAS A TAD SUBTLE.


242
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:54,278
SUBTLETY IS A VIRTUE            
IN ANY FORM.                    


243
00:16:54,347 --> 00:16:59,116
    A NEIGHBOR WHO'S A SCHOLAR  
    OF THE ARTS AND LETTERS.    
    THANK YOU, JAROD.           


244
00:16:59,185 --> 00:17:02,853
    UM, YOU CAN YELL AT ME      
    THROUGH THE WALL ANYTIME.   


245
00:17:02,922 --> 00:17:05,589
AND THANK YOU FOR THE TIP.      


246
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:12,530
YOU WILL DO VERY NICELY HERE.   


247
00:17:41,427 --> 00:17:45,162
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>IN SECONDS,</i>                     
<i>THE VIRUS INVADES THE HOST CELL.</i>


248
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:48,765
- WITH A LEVEL 4 VIRUS,         
  THE RESULTS ARE DEVASTATING.  
- [ Chattering, Laughing ]      


249
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:52,402
<i>THE MUTABA VILLAGE OUTBREAK.</i>    


250
00:17:52,471 --> 00:17:56,874
SUBJECTS BEGIN COUGHING         
ONLY FOUR HOURS AFTER EXPOSURE. 


251
00:17:56,943 --> 00:17:59,810
        INTERNAL BLEEDING       
        COMMENCES AT HOUR 12,   


252
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:02,813
            AND BY HOUR 36,     


253
00:18:02,882 --> 00:18:05,850
        THE SUBJECT COMPLETELY  
        BLEEDS OUT.             


254
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:08,519
        [ Chattering ]          
    <i> GENTLEMEN, YOU CAN IGNORE</i>  
    <i> THE FLIGHT ATTENDANT...</i>    


255
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:10,955
    AS SHE TRIES TO TEACH YOU   
    HOW TO FASTEN THE SEAT BELT,


256
00:18:11,023 --> 00:18:13,390
    BUT WITH THE MUTABA VIRUS   
    AND OTHER LEVEL FOURS,      


257
00:18:13,459 --> 00:18:15,392
        <i> THE KILL RATE IS 90%.</i>  


258
00:18:15,461 --> 00:18:17,462
AND, MAY I ADD,                 
AN AIRBORNE VIRUS...            


259
00:18:17,530 --> 00:18:22,066
COUPLED WITH A PINPRICK         
IN YOUR GLOVE                   
OR A FAULTY SEAL...             


260
00:18:22,134 --> 00:18:24,234
SENDS YOU INTO THE SLAMMER,     
AND FROM THERE...               


261
00:18:24,303 --> 00:18:27,204
IT'S AN EXPRESS                 
STRAIGHT TO THE SUBMARINE.      


262
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:29,206
        LIGHTS.                 


263
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:31,242
<i>THANK YOU FOR</i>                   
<i>THE SAFETY REVIEW, DR. REILLY.</i>  


264
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,878
    YOU MISLED THEM BACK THERE. 


265
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:38,582
        YOU AND JON FLORENCE    
        DID DEVELOP A VACCINE   
        FOR THE CAHUENGA VIRUS. 


266
00:18:38,651 --> 00:18:42,753
    WE GOT LUCKY ON THAT.       
    BUT WITH EBOLA OR MUTABA--  


267
00:18:42,821 --> 00:18:44,855
            WELL, I HAVE        
            TO KEEP 'EM HONEST. 


268
00:18:44,923 --> 00:18:48,959
<i>I'M SORRY ABOUT DR. FLORENCE.</i>   
<i>YOU MUST MISS HIM.</i>              


269
00:18:49,027 --> 00:18:52,563
- VERY MUCH.                    
- FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,       
  DR. FLORENCE WAS A FAMILY MAN.


270
00:18:52,632 --> 00:18:55,199
    -<i> HARDLY THE TYPE</i>           
     <i> TO JUST UP AND LEAVE.</i>     
    - HE WAS A GOOD MAN.        


271
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:57,368
    OF ALL PEOPLE,              
    YOU TWO SHOULD KNOW THAT... 


272
00:18:57,436 --> 00:19:01,805
    AWFUL THINGS SWIRL BENEATH  
    THE HEALTHIEST OF EXTERIORS.


273
00:19:01,874 --> 00:19:06,410
JON CONFIDED IN ME THAT         
THINGS AT HOME WEREN'T OPTIMAL. 


274
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:11,215
<i>HE NEVER WENT INTO SPECIFICS,</i>   
<i>BUT HE CERTAINLY ENJOYED WORKING</i>
<i>THE EXTRA HOURS HERE...</i>         


275
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:14,585
    RATHER THAN BEING AT HOME.  


276
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:18,155
        <i> THIS IS AN AIRBORNE</i>    
        <i> LEVEL 4 VIRUS.</i>         
        <i> LET'S BE ON OUR TOES.</i>  


277
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:20,991
        COMMENCING              
        PHASE TWO DISSECTION.   


278
00:19:23,129 --> 00:19:26,663
WE ARE 72 HOURS AFTER EXPIRATION
BY MUTABA STRAIN "B,"           


279
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:29,133
<i>SUBJECT 247.</i>                    


280
00:19:32,639 --> 00:19:34,271
            - WALTER.           
            - GOOD GOD!         


281
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,807
        DECON!                  
            COME ON.            
            LET'S MOVE IT. GO!  


282
00:19:36,876 --> 00:19:39,142
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>               
    OKAY, LET'S REMAIN CALM.    


283
00:19:42,047 --> 00:19:43,981
    PROCEED WITH DECON SHOWER.  


284
00:19:44,050 --> 00:19:49,186
    - COMING THROUGH.           
    -<i> [ Garber ]</i>                
     <i> STAY CALM. YOU'LL BE FINE.</i>


285
00:19:49,255 --> 00:19:51,188
                    CODE DENIED.
DAMN IT!                        
THE CODE ISN'T WORKING!         


286
00:19:51,257 --> 00:19:53,324
    HERE, LET ME.               


287
00:19:55,328 --> 00:19:57,828
            [ Electronic Voice ]
            CODE ACCEPTED.      


288
00:19:59,932 --> 00:20:01,965
        GET THE GLOVE OFF.      
INOCULATE.                      


289
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,034
        HURRY UP.               


290
00:20:09,942 --> 00:20:13,176
        NO SKIN BREAKS.         
        THE BLOOD MUST'VE BEEN  
        FROM THE SAMPLE.        


291
00:20:13,245 --> 00:20:16,680
WELL DONE, EVERYBODY.           
EVERYTHING BY THE NUMBERS.      


292
00:20:16,749 --> 00:20:19,483
WE'LL REVIEW                    
THE SECURITY TAPE TOMORROW.     


293
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:24,521
WELL, YOU HANDLED               
THAT SIMULATION AS IF IT WERE   
COMPLETELY REAL, JAROD.         


294
00:20:24,591 --> 00:20:26,323
        WELL, I'VE HAD          
        A LOT OF PRACTICE, SIR. 


295
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:29,559
        WHO CHANGED             
        THE SLAMMER ACCESS CODE?


296
00:20:29,628 --> 00:20:31,862
LISA, THE FEWER PEOPLE          
THAT HAVE THE CODE, THE         
FEWER PEOPLE THAT ARE AT RISK.  


297
00:20:31,931 --> 00:20:35,433
I DON'T WANT ANYBODY            
NEAR THE SLAMMER                
UNLESS THEY HAVE TO BE.         


298
00:20:35,501 --> 00:20:38,702
            IT'S YOUR FUNERAL.  
NO, IT'S HIS.                   


299
00:20:41,441 --> 00:20:45,008
        GARBER'S THE ONLY PERSON
        THAT HAS THE ACCESS CODE
        TO THE SLAMMER?         


300
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,144
AND THE SUBMARINE.              


301
00:21:22,681 --> 00:21:25,716
OH, JON.                        
HOW'S MY GODDAUGHTER?           


302
00:21:25,785 --> 00:21:29,619
ABOUT TO TURN SIX, BUT          
SHE THINKS SHE'S 16. I HOPE     
YOU CAN MAKE IT TO HER PARTY.   


303
00:21:29,689 --> 00:21:31,621
I WOULDN'T MISS IT              
FOR THE WORLD.                  


304
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:36,694
I'VE PROCEEDED WITH             
THE AUTOPSY ON THE MONKEY.      
LOOK AT THE LIVER.              


305
00:21:42,402 --> 00:21:44,668
                MUSH.           


306
00:21:44,737 --> 00:21:46,970
        THIS VIRUS HAS MUTATED. 


307
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:52,576
        WE'LL FINISH THIS       
        FIRST THING MONDAY.     


308
00:23:25,171 --> 00:23:29,306
    FORGIVE ME, FATHER,         
    FOR I HAVE SINNED.          


309
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:31,375
        IT'S BEEN--             


310
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:35,613
        OH, MY GOD--            


311
00:23:35,681 --> 00:23:38,314
    33 YEARS SINCE              
    MY LAST CONFESSION.         


312
00:23:43,655 --> 00:23:45,589
I HAVE BETRAYED A FRIEND.       


313
00:23:45,658 --> 00:23:47,591
    THEN YOU MUST SEEK          
    HIS FORGIVENESS.            


314
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:51,428
    MM-MMM.                     
    HE HAS SHUT ME OUT.         


315
00:23:51,497 --> 00:23:55,265
    YOU'RE TROUBLED             
    BY SOMETHING ELSE.          


316
00:23:55,334 --> 00:23:58,102
    HAVE YOU PRAYED TO THE LORD 
    FOR FORGIVENESS?            


317
00:23:58,170 --> 00:24:01,438
NOT EVEN HE CAN FORGIVE ME      
FOR WHAT I'VE DONE.             


318
00:24:07,313 --> 00:24:09,680
        LOOK AT THE LIVER.      


319
00:24:12,451 --> 00:24:16,687
[ Jon ]                         
MUSH. THIS VIRUS HAS MUTATED.   
            MM-HMM.             


320
00:24:16,756 --> 00:24:19,456
            IT'S LIKE           
            THE CAHUENGA VIRUS, 
            BUT WORSE.          


321
00:24:19,524 --> 00:24:23,193
THIS IS A LEVEL 5 VIRUS.        
WHAT THE HELL HAVE YOU DONE?    


322
00:24:23,262 --> 00:24:25,195
            YOU MADE EBOLA      
            LOOK LIKE THE FLU.  


323
00:24:25,264 --> 00:24:28,599
- I'VE BEEN WORKING ON IT,      
  GENETICALLY.                  
- NO, YOU'VE BEEN PLAYING GOD.  


324
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:30,601
             WE GOTTA SHUT DOWN 
             THIS PROJECT NOW.  


325
00:24:30,669 --> 00:24:33,437
            I'M DESTROYING IT.  
            YOU CAN'T.          


326
00:24:33,506 --> 00:24:35,439
                    YES, I CAN. 
        I WON'T LET YOU.        


327
00:24:35,508 --> 00:24:38,241
        LET GO OF MY AIR HOSE!  


328
00:24:39,445 --> 00:24:41,244
    I WON'T LET YOU.            
        LET GO OF MY AIR HOSE!  


329
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:44,080
        I WON'T LET YOU.        
        LET GO OF MY AIR HOSE!  
         LET GO OF MY AIR HOSE! 


330
00:24:44,149 --> 00:24:47,117
             MY GOD, WALTER,    
             YOU'VE KILLED ME!  


331
00:24:47,186 --> 00:24:49,153
QUICK,                          
INTO THE DECON SHOWER.          


332
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:52,522
        [ Alarm Blaring ]       
THE LAB IS FULL OF THE VIRUS.   


333
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:54,825
STAY CALM. DON'T PANIC.         


334
00:24:54,893 --> 00:24:59,230
PRESSURE FAILURE!               
GET INTO THE SLAMMER.           
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.            


335
00:25:45,945 --> 00:25:50,880
HELLO, JON.                     
I WAS AFRAID I'D FIND YOU HERE. 


336
00:25:52,951 --> 00:25:55,185
<i>♪♪ [ Cello ]</i>                    


337
00:26:13,872 --> 00:26:16,973
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>HANSEL, YOU ARE DRIVING ME NUTS!</i>


338
00:26:17,043 --> 00:26:19,043
<i>SHUT UP!</i>                        


339
00:26:29,321 --> 00:26:31,254
INTERESTING INTERPRETATION.     


340
00:26:31,323 --> 00:26:35,859
<i>[ Pounding On Wall ]</i>            
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>YOU SUCK!</i>                       


341
00:26:35,927 --> 00:26:37,861
    YOU'RE A POLITE NEIGHBOR,   
    JAROD,                      


342
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:41,331
            BUT I FEAR          
            THE CULTURAL DWARVES
            ARE RIGHT.          


343
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,734
                I'M TERRIBLE.   


344
00:26:43,802 --> 00:26:46,403
IT TAKES A LONG TIME            
TO MASTER MUSIC, BEN.           


345
00:26:46,472 --> 00:26:50,174
        A LIFETIME WOULD NOT BE 
        LONG ENOUGH FOR ME.     


346
00:26:50,242 --> 00:26:52,209
    MY MUSIC KILLS PLANT LIFE.  


347
00:26:54,413 --> 00:26:57,213
            I'M SALIERI         
            TO MOZART, JAROD.   


348
00:26:57,282 --> 00:27:02,686
    I CURSE GOD FOR BESTOWING ME
    WITH MEDIOCRE ABILITY.      


349
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:20,270
                ♪♪ [ Music Box ]


350
00:27:20,339 --> 00:27:22,772
<i>WHAT ARE THESE?</i>                 


351
00:27:22,842 --> 00:27:27,578
            TRIFLES, LARKS.     
            POINTLESS EXERCISES.


352
00:27:32,618 --> 00:27:34,684
DID YOU MAKE THESE?             


353
00:27:34,753 --> 00:27:36,919
                    YES.        


354
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:39,289
BEN, THESE ARE EXQUISITE.       


355
00:27:39,358 --> 00:27:41,758
        YOUR COMPLIMENT         
        IS APPRECIATED, JAROD.  


356
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:44,394
            BUT, ART IT IS NOT. 


357
00:27:44,462 --> 00:27:47,164
    ART IS MANY THINGS.         


358
00:27:47,232 --> 00:27:50,334
    SOME CHOOSE A BRUSH,        
     SOME A BOW,                


359
00:27:50,402 --> 00:27:54,938
    SOME A PEN,                 
    AND SOME... CHOOSE GLASS.   


360
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:57,307
            WHAT DO YOU MEAN?   


361
00:27:57,376 --> 00:28:02,679
MAYBE THE WAY YOU CREATE        
IS THROUGH THESE PIECES         
RATHER THAN THAT.               


362
00:28:02,748 --> 00:28:05,348
<i>YOU SAID IT YOURSELF, BEN.</i>      


363
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:09,119
    SOMETIMES AN ARTIST         
    NEEDS TO STRETCH.           


364
00:28:11,223 --> 00:28:14,624
            [ Beeping ]         


365
00:28:30,976 --> 00:28:33,409
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>SYDNEY, I'M SCARED.</i>             
<i>I CAN'T DO THIS.</i>                


366
00:28:33,478 --> 00:28:37,013
<i>[ Young Sydney ]</i>                
<i>YOU HAVE TO, JAROD.</i>             


367
00:28:37,082 --> 00:28:41,017
        THERE'S SMOKE.          
        PEOPLE ARE SCREAMING.   


368
00:28:41,086 --> 00:28:44,021
        SYDNEY, THEY'RE BURNING!
        THEY'RE BURNING!        


369
00:28:44,089 --> 00:28:46,823
MAKE IT STOP!                   
 MAKE THE BURNING STOP!         


370
00:28:46,892 --> 00:28:48,859
        - JAROD!                
        - MAKE IT STOP!         


371
00:28:48,928 --> 00:28:51,728
        NO, GO AWAY!            
        LEAVE ME ALONE!         


372
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:56,899
        IT'S ALL RIGHT, JAROD.  
         IT'S ALL RIGHT.        


373
00:28:58,571 --> 00:29:00,771
                    AAH!        


374
00:29:00,839 --> 00:29:03,306
IT'S ALL OVER, JAROD.           
 IT'S ALL RIGHT.                


375
00:29:03,375 --> 00:29:07,010
                I WANT MY DADDY.
THE CODE WORD                   
MAKES IT STOP, JAROD.           


376
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:10,913
YOU DIDN'T USE THE CODE WORD    
WE CAME UP WITH.                
    I SAID, I WANT MY DAD.      


377
00:29:10,982 --> 00:29:12,916
LET ME.                         


378
00:29:12,985 --> 00:29:17,154
JAROD, REMEMBER.                


379
00:29:17,222 --> 00:29:20,523
WHEN YOU'RE DOING               
THE SIMULATION                  
AND YOU BECOME FRIGHTENED...    


380
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:25,261
    AND WANNA STOP,             
    SAY, "REFUGE."              


381
00:29:25,331 --> 00:29:28,699
ALL RIGHT?                      
MM-HMM?                         


382
00:29:36,976 --> 00:29:39,042
                REFUGE.         


383
00:29:58,697 --> 00:30:01,632
                    [ Beeping ] 


384
00:30:12,344 --> 00:30:15,212
<i>[ Miss Parker Sneezing ]</i>        


385
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,381
        [ Coughing ]            


386
00:30:19,784 --> 00:30:21,818
HE CONTACTED ME.                


387
00:30:23,222 --> 00:30:25,522
NO SECRETS.                     


388
00:30:25,591 --> 00:30:28,158
                WHY THE SUDDEN  
                CHANGE OF HEART?


389
00:30:28,227 --> 00:30:31,828
LATELY, I'VE BEEN SEEING THINGS 
FROM ANOTHER ANGLE,             


390
00:30:31,897 --> 00:30:34,498
AND MAYBE IT'S BEST             
IF YOU GET HIM.                 


391
00:31:23,148 --> 00:31:26,449
        DR. HOFFMAN,            
        DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?   


392
00:31:28,220 --> 00:31:30,152
WHAT'S UP?                      


393
00:31:30,221 --> 00:31:32,422
    WHAT DO YOU MAKE OF THIS?   
    HMM?                        


394
00:31:32,490 --> 00:31:35,525
WELL, LET'S SEE.                


395
00:31:35,594 --> 00:31:40,863
LIQUEFICATION OF ORGANS,        
BLOOD SECRETION THROUGH         
SKIN PORES, LOSS OF HAIR.       


396
00:31:40,932 --> 00:31:42,865
LOOKS LIKE AN ADVANCED          
VERSION OF MUTABA.              


397
00:31:42,934 --> 00:31:47,470
        THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT   
        UNTIL I FOUND<i> THIS.</i>     


398
00:31:49,774 --> 00:31:51,974
I'VE NEVER SEEN THIS BEFORE.    
DID YOU CROSS-CHECK IT?         


399
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:54,144
            AGAINST EVERY SAMPLE
            ON RECORD.          


400
00:31:54,212 --> 00:31:56,246
THERE'S OVER 3,000 ON RECORD.   


401
00:31:56,314 --> 00:31:58,314
    IT DID GET A LITTLE TEDIOUS 
    AFTER THE FIRST 800.        


402
00:32:01,052 --> 00:32:03,686
            [ Chattering ]      
<i>[ Hoffman ]</i>                     
<i>MY GOD.</i>                         


403
00:32:03,755 --> 00:32:05,821
JAROD, THIS IS WORSE THAN       
ANY LEVEL 4 I'VE EVER SEEN.     


404
00:32:05,890 --> 00:32:08,725
        - IT'S A LEVEL 5.       
        - WHAT?                 


405
00:32:08,794 --> 00:32:10,726
THERE'S A LEVEL 5 HERE?         


406
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:13,496
        IT'S A SAMPLE OFF A BODY
        IN THE SUBMARINE.       


407
00:32:13,565 --> 00:32:17,500
WAIT. H-HOW DID YOU GET         
IN THE SUBMARINE?               
ONLY GAR--                      


408
00:32:17,569 --> 00:32:19,168
                GO. GO.         


409
00:32:19,237 --> 00:32:20,770
GARBER HAS THE CODE.            


410
00:32:23,442 --> 00:32:26,643
            IS ALL RESEARCH HERE
            SANCTIONED BY       
            A GOVERNING BODY?   


411
00:32:29,414 --> 00:32:31,548
            WHICH PROJECT ISN'T?


412
00:32:34,052 --> 00:32:38,187
IT'S ONLY HEARSAY,              
BUT I TRUST THE SOURCE.         


413
00:32:38,256 --> 00:32:41,991
GARBER WAS WORKING              
ON SOME RESEARCH.               
I-I DON'T KNOW WHAT.            


414
00:32:43,494 --> 00:32:46,095
        WHAT ELSE DID           
        JON FLORENCE TELL YOU?  


415
00:32:47,598 --> 00:32:49,532
        HOW'D YOU KNOW          
        JON WAS THE SOURCE?     


416
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,867
    BESIDES GARBER,             
    HE WAS THE ONLY PERSON...   


417
00:32:51,936 --> 00:32:53,970
        THAT KNEW EVERYTHING    
         THAT WAS GOING ON HERE.


418
00:32:56,874 --> 00:32:58,808
    WHAT ELSE DID HE TELL YOU?  


419
00:32:58,876 --> 00:33:03,913
THAT GARBER WAS WORKING         
ON SOME RADICAL MUTATIONS       
OF A LEVEL 5.                   


420
00:33:03,982 --> 00:33:08,752
HE SAID IT STARTED OUT GOOD,    
BUT IT GOT CORRUPTED.           


421
00:33:10,188 --> 00:33:13,255
    JON SAID GOD                
    WOULD NEVER FORGIVE HIM...  


422
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:15,257
        IF HE LET               
        THIS PROJECT CONTINUE.  


423
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:19,128
            WELL, UNFORTUNATELY 
            FOR JON FLORENCE,   


424
00:33:19,197 --> 00:33:21,130
        HE NEVER HAD THE CHANCE 
        TO STOP IT.             


425
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:25,267
        OH, MY GOD.             


426
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:28,171
[ Jon ]                         
MUSH. THIS VIRUS HAS MUTATED.   


427
00:33:28,239 --> 00:33:30,906
        MM-HMM.                 


428
00:33:30,975 --> 00:33:33,142
    WE'LL FINISH THIS           
    FIRST THING MONDAY.         


429
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:34,944
            <i> [ Tape Rewinding ]</i> 


430
00:33:55,834 --> 00:33:59,035
I'M GUESSING BETWEEN THE KNOB,  
THE MOUTHPIECE AND THE          
CITY WATER YOU'RE DRINKING,     


431
00:33:59,103 --> 00:34:02,572
            THERE'S ENOUGH GERMS
            TO KILL A COCKROACH.


432
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:07,176
DR. REILLY. HI.                 
YEAH, YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.    


433
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:10,213
I DEAL WITH THE GERMS I CAN,    
BUT SOMETHING TELLS ME...       


434
00:34:10,281 --> 00:34:12,514
I WOULDN'T LAST LONG            
LIVING IN A PLASTIC BUBBLE.     


435
00:34:12,583 --> 00:34:15,184
            EVEN ONE EQUIPPED   
            WITH A DECON SHOWER?


436
00:34:18,656 --> 00:34:21,624
        IT WAS AN EXCELLENT     
        PERFORMANCE, JEFF.      


437
00:34:21,692 --> 00:34:23,626
LOOK, I-I DON'T KNOW            
WHAT YOU MEAN.                  


438
00:34:23,694 --> 00:34:26,996
        ARE YOU GONNA MAKE ME   
        ENHANCE THE IMAGE       
        SO I CAN SEE YOUR FACE? 


439
00:34:43,548 --> 00:34:45,481
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE      
NOT BEING ABLE TO SLEEP?        


440
00:34:45,549 --> 00:34:48,418
            YOU'D BE SURPRISED. 


441
00:34:48,486 --> 00:34:50,420
I WATCHED A MAN                 
BEG FOR HIS LIFE.               


442
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:53,222
    HE BEGGED TO SEE            
    HIS WIFE AND KID AGAIN,     
    AND I--                     


443
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:56,326
    I-- I DIDN'T HELP HIM.      


444
00:34:56,394 --> 00:35:00,363
    I KNOW JON FLORENCE         
    GOT INFECTED, I KNOW        
    HIS BODY'S IN THE SUBMARINE,


445
00:35:00,431 --> 00:35:02,631
    AND I KNOW THAT YOU HELPED  
    GARBER DOCTOR THIS TAPE.    


446
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:06,068
    BUT WHAT I CAN'T FIGURE OUT 
    IS WHY.                     


447
00:35:06,137 --> 00:35:08,604
BECAUSE IT WAS MY FAULT,        
THAT'S WHY.                     


448
00:35:10,742 --> 00:35:13,576
    I-I WAS WORKING LATE        
    LIKE JON AND DR. GARBER,    


449
00:35:13,645 --> 00:35:16,412
        AND I-I SAW JON         
        COME INTO THE SLAMMER,  


450
00:35:16,481 --> 00:35:20,249
        AND HE-HE--             
        HE LOOKED SO FRIGHTENED.


451
00:35:23,722 --> 00:35:28,858
THE DECON SHOWER LOST PRESSURE, 


452
00:35:28,926 --> 00:35:30,859
AND THAT IS MY JOB              
TO MAKE SURE THAT IT DOESN'T.   


453
00:35:30,929 --> 00:35:33,996
        THAT-THAT IS MY JOB,    
        DR. REILLY.             


454
00:35:34,064 --> 00:35:37,533
AND THEN GARBER WENT BALLISTIC, 
AND HE BLAMED ME                
FOR JON'S CONTAMINATION.        


455
00:35:37,602 --> 00:35:43,306
YOU KNOW, I-I HAVE NEVER        
SEEN A VIRUS DO WHAT IT DID     
TO HIM, OR SO QUICKLY.          


456
00:35:43,375 --> 00:35:45,574
    AND THAT'S WHY YOU WON'T    
    GO PAST LEVEL 2 ANYMORE.    


457
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:50,145
        IT'S JUST THAT JON--    


458
00:35:50,214 --> 00:35:52,147
    HE BEGGED ME TO GET         
    HIS WIFE AND KID,           


459
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:56,285
AND-AND GARBER--                
GARBER TOLD ME TO KEEP IT QUIET.


460
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:59,188
    HE SAID THAT--              
    THAT THE AUTHORITIES        
    WOULD HAVE TO BE CALLED...  


461
00:35:59,256 --> 00:36:01,123
    AND THAT THEY WOULD         
    SHUT DOWN THE FACILITY,     


462
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:04,293
    AND THAT MORE LIVES WOULD   
    BE LOST BECAUSE OF MY ERROR.


463
00:36:04,362 --> 00:36:09,565
JON FLORENCE DID NOT DIE BECAUSE
OF YOU OR THE DECON SHOWER.     


464
00:36:09,633 --> 00:36:12,568
    HE DIED BECAUSE             
    WALTER GARBER MURDERED HIM. 


465
00:36:35,459 --> 00:36:37,427
        HELLO, BUTCHER BOB'S?   


466
00:36:37,495 --> 00:36:41,930
    I'D LIKE TO ORDER           
    A DOZEN PIG LIVERS, PLEASE. 
    YES, A DOZEN.               


467
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:07,990
                SAY "CHEESE."   


468
00:37:30,181 --> 00:37:32,015
            GOOD MORNING, CLASS.


469
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:36,619
    TODAY'S LESSON TAKES US     
    INTO THE FASCINATING WORLD  
    OF COCKROACHES.             


470
00:37:36,688 --> 00:37:38,620
        WALTER?                 
                <i> YES?</i>           


471
00:37:38,690 --> 00:37:40,289
                    IT'S JAROD. 


472
00:37:40,358 --> 00:37:44,026
I'VE MADE A VERY                
INTERESTING DISCOVERY THAT      
I THINK YOU SHOULD CHECK OUT.   


473
00:37:44,095 --> 00:37:47,563
    WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?          
        WELL, IT'S STILL        
        TOO EARLY TO BE SURE,   


474
00:37:47,631 --> 00:37:50,032
        BUT I THINK I FOUND     
        A VACCINE FOR MUTABA.   


475
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:53,803
I'LL-I'LL MEET YOU IN THE LAB   
IN AN HOUR, JAROD.              
                    PERFECT.    


476
00:38:01,379 --> 00:38:03,412
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?              


477
00:38:09,387 --> 00:38:12,521
    WHERE'D YOU GET THE SAMPLE? 


478
00:38:12,590 --> 00:38:14,523
FROM THIS LIVER.                


479
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:16,826
        MY GOD, MAN!            
        IT'S AN AIRBORNE VIRUS! 


480
00:38:16,894 --> 00:38:20,096
WALTER, YOUR AIR HOSE.          


481
00:38:20,165 --> 00:38:22,498
                <i> HIT THE ALARM!</i> 
                <i> HELP ME!</i>       
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>               


482
00:38:22,567 --> 00:38:24,801
                HELP ME!        


483
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:30,105
            GOD!                


484
00:38:31,842 --> 00:38:34,443
    OH! THERE'S PRESSURE FAILURE
    IN THE DECON LINE!          


485
00:38:34,512 --> 00:38:37,013
WELL, YOU'D BETTER              
GET INTO THE SLAMMER, SIR.      


486
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:46,922
        <i> [ Electronic Voice ]</i>   
        <i> CODE ACCEPTED.</i>         


487
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:50,393
        WHERE IS EVERYBODY?     
         WHERE ARE THE DOCTORS? 


488
00:38:50,461 --> 00:38:52,461
                    BAYTOS!     


489
00:38:54,732 --> 00:38:57,265
    THERE'S NOBODY HERE, SIR.   


490
00:38:57,334 --> 00:39:00,535
    - I SENT THEM ALL HOME.     
    - JAROD, YOU'VE KILLED ME!  


491
00:39:00,604 --> 00:39:05,841
    RELAX, WALTER. I TOLD YOU.  
    I MADE A LITTLE DISCOVERY.  


492
00:39:05,910 --> 00:39:10,446
IT'S A DERIVATIVE CROSS         
BETWEEN YOUR CAHUENGA VIRUS     
AND THE RIFT VALLEY STRAIN.     


493
00:39:10,514 --> 00:39:13,716
    AN ANTI-VIRUS.              
    IT SHUTS YOUR STRAIN DOWN.  


494
00:39:13,785 --> 00:39:16,985
        GIVE IT TO ME, PLEASE.  


495
00:39:17,054 --> 00:39:19,655
    - I CAN'T.                  
    - JAROD, PLEASE, HELP ME!   


496
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:21,990
LIKE YOU HELPED JON FLORENCE... 


497
00:39:22,059 --> 00:39:25,394
BY EXPOSING HIM TO              
A LEVEL 5 WITHOUT ANY CURE?     


498
00:39:25,463 --> 00:39:26,963
        WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?   


499
00:39:27,031 --> 00:39:29,765
WELL, I SURE AS HELL            
AM NOT FLORENCE NIGHTINGALE.    


500
00:39:29,834 --> 00:39:33,069
BUT, THEN AGAIN,                
NEITHER ARE YOU.                


501
00:39:33,138 --> 00:39:35,938
HOW LONG, WALTER?               


502
00:39:36,007 --> 00:39:39,474
HOW LONG BEFORE JON FLORENCE    
STARTED TO SHOW SYMPTOMS?       


503
00:39:39,544 --> 00:39:42,144
<i>HOW LONG BEFORE</i>                 
<i>THE INTERNAL BLEEDING STARTED?</i>  


504
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:46,582
HOW LONG BEFORE                 
HIS BRAIN TISSUE                
STARTED TO LEAK INTO HIS EARS?  


505
00:39:46,650 --> 00:39:51,186
HOW LONG BEFORE HIS INTERNAL    
ORGANS STARTED TO LIQUEFY?      
HOW LONG, WALTER?               


506
00:39:51,255 --> 00:39:54,090
        GIVE ME THAT SYRINGE.   
<i>WHY?</i>                            


507
00:39:54,158 --> 00:39:58,427
        JON FLORENCE            
        NEVER HAD THIS OPTION.  
        WHY SHOULD YOU?         


508
00:39:58,496 --> 00:40:01,096
- JAROD, IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.    
- HE KNEW HE WAS GOING TO DIE.  


509
00:40:01,165 --> 00:40:05,167
AND I'LL BET THE LAST THING     
HE WANTED TO DO WAS JUST TO     
SEE HIS FAMILY ONE MORE TIME... 


510
00:40:05,236 --> 00:40:08,037
TO SAY GOOD-BYE TO HIS WIFE     
AND TO HIS CHILD.               


511
00:40:08,105 --> 00:40:10,806
    BUT YOU COULDN'T            
    GIVE HIM THAT PEACE,        
    COULD YOU, WALTER?          


512
00:40:10,875 --> 00:40:13,842
<i>BECAUSE THEN THE TRUTH</i>          
<i>WOULD COME OUT ABOUT HOW</i>        
<i>YOU WERE TRYING TO PLAY GOD...</i>  


513
00:40:13,911 --> 00:40:16,044
<i>WITH ALL THESE</i>                  
<i>VIRAL EXPERIMENTS.</i>              


514
00:40:16,113 --> 00:40:18,481
YOU TOOK JON FLORENCE'S LIFE,   


515
00:40:18,549 --> 00:40:20,849
    AND YOU RUINED              
    HIS FAMILY'S AS WELL.       


516
00:40:20,918 --> 00:40:24,120
    - THAT IS NO ACCIDENT.      
    - ALL RIGHT, I DID IT.      
      I ADMIT IT. I KILLED HIM! 


517
00:40:24,188 --> 00:40:27,289
            <i> THE-THE RESEARCH</i>   
            <i> WAS VERY VALUABLE.</i> 


518
00:40:27,358 --> 00:40:31,293
- PLEASE, GIVE ME THE VACCINE!  
- ALL RIGHT, WALTER.            


519
00:40:31,362 --> 00:40:34,496
    BUT I WILL WARN YOU.        
    IT'S ONLY SUGAR WATER.      


520
00:40:34,565 --> 00:40:36,899
                    SUGAR WATER?


521
00:40:36,968 --> 00:40:39,034
    I DON'T KNOW HOW            
    TO MAKE A VACCINE.          


522
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,637
    YOU SEE,                    
    I'M NOT REALLY A VIROLOGIST.


523
00:40:41,705 --> 00:40:45,373
    - THE TRUTH IS, THIS PLACE  
      GIVES ME THE CREEPS.      
    - WHAT?                     


524
00:40:45,442 --> 00:40:49,478
        YOU CAN CHECK OUT       
        ANYTIME YOU LIKE,       
        BUT YOU CAN NEVER LEAVE.


525
00:40:49,546 --> 00:40:52,514
        NO! NO!                 
        DON'T LEAVE ME! JAROD!  


526
00:40:52,583 --> 00:40:55,250
        <i> [ Over Monitor ]</i>       
        <i> JAROD! COME BACK HERE!</i> 


527
00:40:55,319 --> 00:40:58,353
                <i> JAROD!</i>         
                <i> WAIT, DON'T!</i>   


528
00:40:58,422 --> 00:41:01,590
<i>PLEASE, DON'T LEAVE ME HERE!</i>    
<i> PLEASE, DON'T!</i>                 


529
00:41:01,658 --> 00:41:04,560
            HELP! HELP!         


530
00:41:04,629 --> 00:41:07,295
AREN'T YOU GONNA TELL HIM       
YOU DIDN'T REALLY INFECT HIM?   
        <i> [ Shouting Continues ]</i> 


531
00:41:07,364 --> 00:41:11,500
    NAH. WHY DON'T YOU DO IT?   
    IN 48 HOURS.                


532
00:41:11,568 --> 00:41:13,569
                <i> HELP! PLEASE!</i>  


533
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:16,238
                <i> SOMEBODY, HELP!</i>


534
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:18,507
    AFTER THE POLICE GET THIS.  
                    <i> HELP ME!</i>   


535
00:41:18,575 --> 00:41:24,046
            <i> OH, NO! GOD!</i>       
             <i> OH, GOD, HELP ME!</i> 


536
00:41:24,115 --> 00:41:27,116
                    <i> COME BACK!</i> 
                     <i> COME BACK!</i>


537
00:41:27,185 --> 00:41:29,418
                <i> JAROD! JAROD!</i>  


538
00:41:33,424 --> 00:41:35,824
    WHAT IS THAT SMELL?         
            I CAN'T SMELL.      


539
00:41:35,893 --> 00:41:37,793
        GO LEFT.                
        YOU TAKE THAT ROOM.     


540
00:41:46,537 --> 00:41:48,904
        GOOD MORNING, CLASS.    


541
00:41:48,972 --> 00:41:53,108
    TODAY'S LESSON TAKES US     
    INTO THE FASCINATING WORLD  
    OF COCKROACHES.             


542
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:56,912
    - NOTHING. HE'S GONE.       
    - YES, BUT NOT FORGOTTEN.   


543
00:41:56,981 --> 00:42:00,749
    - [ Groans ]                
    - THIS IS A BUG MOTEL.      


544
00:42:00,817 --> 00:42:03,218
        WHEN THE HORMONES       
        OFF A ROACH'S BODY,     


545
00:42:03,287 --> 00:42:06,088
    <i> WHICH IS THE WET STUFF</i>     
    <i> YOU JUST WALKED THROUGH,</i>   


546
00:42:06,157 --> 00:42:09,958
    <i> COMBINES WITH THE STICKY</i>   
    <i> STUFF INSIDE OF THE BOX,</i>   
    <i> WHICH YOU ARE STANDING IN,</i> 


547
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:12,794
        IT FORMS A BOND...      


548
00:42:12,863 --> 00:42:15,630
WHICH IS STRONGER               
THAN EPOXY.                     


549
00:42:18,802 --> 00:42:21,303
    WELCOME TO THE WORLD'S      
    LARGEST BUG MOTEL.          


550
00:42:21,371 --> 00:42:23,105
        YOU SON OF A BITCH.     


551
00:42:23,174 --> 00:42:26,441
        ENJOY YOUR STAY.        
        CLASS DISMISSED.        


552
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:28,511
I'M STUCK.                      


553
00:42:29,513 --> 00:42:33,816
<i>♪♪ [ Trumpet ]</i>                  


554
00:42:33,885 --> 00:42:36,218
<i>[ Pounding On Wall ]</i>            
<i>[ Dog Barking ]</i>                 


555
00:42:56,507 --> 00:42:59,674
         CHIVAS ON THE ROCKS.   
         ONE ICE CUBE.          


556
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:01,744
    CLEVER WAY                  
    OF CONTACTING ME, SYDNEY.   


557
00:43:01,812 --> 00:43:04,146
            NO ONE AT THE CENTRE
            WOULD'VE EVER KNOWN 
            WHAT THIS MEANT.    


558
00:43:07,651 --> 00:43:09,985
I HAD TO SEE YOU FACE-TO-FACE.  


559
00:43:10,054 --> 00:43:12,288
                DID MISS PARKER 
                TAKE THE BAIT?  


560
00:43:12,357 --> 00:43:15,825
        PRESUMABLY.             


561
00:43:15,893 --> 00:43:17,826
I HAVE TO ASK YOU FOR SOMETHING.


562
00:43:19,296 --> 00:43:21,563
        YOU'RE IN NO POSITION   
        TO ASK ME FOR ANYTHING. 


563
00:43:21,632 --> 00:43:23,899
    NOT EVEN YOUR FORGIVENESS?  


564
00:43:25,736 --> 00:43:28,904
- WHAT?                         
- FOR KEEPING YOU IN THE CENTRE.


565
00:43:28,973 --> 00:43:30,905
FOR THE LIES ALL THESE YEARS.   


566
00:43:34,878 --> 00:43:36,878
DID YOU SEND ME THIS?           


567
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:41,317
            NO, I DID NOT.      


568
00:43:43,888 --> 00:43:46,354
    PARKER DID                  
    WITH YOUR NAME ON IT.       


569
00:43:46,423 --> 00:43:48,890
                WHAT IS IT?     
<i>REMINDERS.</i>                      


570
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:54,696
    ISSUES I MUST TAKE UP       
    WITH MYSELF,                


571
00:43:54,765 --> 00:43:56,765
            GOD,                


572
00:43:58,202 --> 00:44:00,202
        AND WITH YOU.           


573
00:44:16,087 --> 00:44:19,354
    - IT'S TOO LATE.            
    - I COME TO YOU             
      WITH AN OLIVE BRANCH.     


574
00:44:21,025 --> 00:44:26,128
        ALL RIGHT.              
        YOU WANT MY FORGIVENESS?


575
00:44:26,196 --> 00:44:28,798
    THEN TELL ME WHAT HAPPENED  
    TO MY MOM AND DAD.          


576
00:44:31,235 --> 00:44:34,369
    I CAN'T.                    
     I DON'T KNOW THE TRUTH.    


577
00:44:34,438 --> 00:44:38,140
        THEN YOU AND THE CENTRE 
        WILL NEVER GET ME BACK. 


578
00:44:38,208 --> 00:44:43,212
AND I CAN'T FORGIVE YOU, SYDNEY.
I CAN'T FORGIVE MYSELF.         


579
00:44:52,189 --> 00:44:56,091
                <i> [ Ringing ]</i>    


580
00:44:56,160 --> 00:45:00,162
            BEN HANSEL.         
    [ Woman ] MR. HANSEL, THIS  
    IS THE CHICAGO PHILHARMONIC.


581
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:03,198
WE RECEIVED THE EXTRAORDINARY   
GLASS SCULPTURE YOU MADE,       


582
00:45:03,267 --> 00:45:06,935
AND WE'D LIKE TO SET UP A TIME  
FOR YOU TO MEET WITH            
OUR MERCHANDISE COORDINATOR.    


583
00:45:07,004 --> 00:45:09,938
        WE HAVE NEXT WEDNESDAY  
        AVAILABLE--             


584
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:20,416
                THANK YOU...    
                FOR EVERYTHING. 


585
00:45:24,588 --> 00:45:27,322
        WHERE WILL YOU GO NOW?  


586
00:45:27,391 --> 00:45:29,358
I'M STARTING A NEW JOB.         


587
00:45:36,099 --> 00:45:38,099
    YOU'VE GOT ROACHES?         


588
00:46:11,802 --> 00:46:12,834
            [ Mews ]            


